upD1igeSa";}i:223;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599252894;}i:224;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1357:"We were photographing bear fishing in a creek on evening when the setting sun caught our attention.  We noticed a lone boar checking out the river contemplating whether to try his hand at catching some salmon.  The sun was casting a beautiful warm light onto the whole scene.  We were already busy photographing the amazing scene when for a moment, a beam shown down from the sun into the frame.  It was gone as quickly as it appeared but we were able to capture this image of a handsome boar along the creek edge.  It was almost as if the light was directing him to the river.  Some times things just line up perfectly!⁣
⁣
